programme.series-desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. Theyre soon wishing theyd gone to Cancun! This Pre­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The films unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DONT LOOK INTO LUGOSIS EYES!
